text: The 2020 United States presidential election in Minnesota was held on Tuesday, November 3, 2020, as part of the 2020 United States presidential election. Former Vice President Joe Biden, and his running mate, junior U.S. Senator Kamala Harris had won 10 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:2020 United States presidential election Category:2020s in Minnesota
title: 2020 United States presidential election in Minnesota
